Thuringia: Zeiss Meditec closer to sales billion
A high demand for medical technology in Asia has boosted the sales of Carl Zeiss Meditec.
In the first nine months of the fiscal year that began in October, group sales rose 6.7 percent to €798.6 million, as the listed company announced in Jena on Friday.
Asia's business grew disproportionately by 17.1 percent.
Earnings before interest and taxes increased from €89.5 million to €110.5 million, according to the interim balance sheet.
The Jenaer Medical Technology Group intends to exceed the sales mark of €1 billion in this financial year, the board confirmed.
Zeiss Meditec manufactures devices and equipment for medical practices and clinics.
The company, which belongs to the optics and electronics group Carl Zeiss (Oberkochen), employs almost 3000 people.
